  "name": "Cutibacterium acnes KPA171202",
  "niche": {
    "entity_count": 120,
    "description": "Curated contaminant-anchor roster x CDS GCF_000008345.1 ASM834v1 (NCBI, public domain). 19 loci: the central-metabolism + propionate-fermentation backbone (glycolysis gap/eno/pyk/pgi/tpiA + pdhA/aceE + the sucC/sucD/fumC route toward propionate + ATP synthase + glpK) + the sebum-degrading lipases (patatin-like phospholipase, GDSL lipase) and host-interaction apparatus (camp2/camp4 CAMP toxins, an exo-alpha-sialidase, a glycerophosphodiester phosphodiesterase). C. acnes KPA171202: 2,560,265 bp / 2,333 ORFs, ~60% GC; aerotolerant anaerobe, slow (>5 d so missed by aerobic checks), sebum dampens disinfectants -> survives antiseptic prep. The immigration kernel reads role + trait levers, not specific genes (ADR-019 S0, Mode A).",
    "temp_optimum": 0.6,
    "parent_key": null,
    "trophic_role": "decomposer"
  },
